---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Journey - Jack Luo"
  description="A place to showcase achievements, journey throughout different fields, and creative works."
  currentPage="journey"
>
  <!-- Creative Content in Hero Slot (goes into #landing section) -->
  <div slot="hero" class="landing-main container-fluid">
    <div class="landing-row row">
      <h3>Creative</h3>
      <p>
        From July 23 onwards, I started writing a book about a guy
        stuck in a liminal space. In 'Limbinal,' I created a world
        where reality blurs, and boundaries between dreams and waking
        life become indistinguishable. I explore things like identity,
        the pursuit of meaning, and "robotic racism". Feel free to read a
        sample
        <a class="a-underline" href="/assets/pdf/limbinal-v12.03.23.pdf">here</a>
        and let me know
        <a href="https://instagram.com/thejackluo">here</a> any
        feedback and questions about the book (bonus points if you know
        publishers).
        <br />
        <br />

        <b>Reading</b>: Check out my complete bookshelf and reading progress
        <a class="a-underline" href="/special/books">here</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've been making music since 10th grade. Most pieces are experimental, but
        I'd recommend you check out a few highlights on my
        <a class="a-underline" href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo">SoundCloud</a>:
        <a
          class="a-underline"
          href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/intersection"
          >intersection</a
        >,
        <a
          class="a-underline"
          href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/memories-v2"
          >memory v2</a
        >,
        <a
          class="a-underline"
          href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/007-mirrox"
          >007 - mirrox</a
        >, and my latest track
        <a
          class="a-underline"
          href="https://soundcloud.com/thejackluo/011-mom"
          >011 - mom</a
        >, which I'm excited about.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also have a <a class="a-underline" href="/special/toy">toy portfolio</a> showcasing
        experimental projects and a <a class="a-underline" href="/special/funny">funny experiment</a>
        with some memorable moments.
        <span style="font-style: italic; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);">
          <b>Note</b>: I'm completely revamping the journey page. See you soon... maybe in a year? ðŸ˜…
        </span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Import journey-specific CSS files */
  @import url('/src/css/journey.css');
  @import url('/src/css/creative.css');

  /* Ensure #landing has proper height for background layers to work */
  /* The Header component provides landing-angular-filter and landing-city divs */
  /* journey.css defines .landing-city with city4.png which matches Header */
  :global(#landing) {
    min-height: 100vh;
    position: relative;
    background-color: black;
  }

  /* landing-container should be absolute positioned (from landing.css) */
  :global(.landing-container) {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    z-index: 1;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* Prevent horizontal scrolling globally */
  :global(html),
  :global(body),
  :global(#fullpage) {
    max-width: 100vw;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* Ensure all containers respect viewport width */
  :global(.container-fluid) {
    max-width: 100%;
    padding-left: 0;
    padding-right: 0;
  }

  /* Ensure rows don't overflow */
  :global(.row) {
    margin-left: 0;
    margin-right: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  /* Override creative-container absolute positioning that causes gaps */
  /* This prevents any creative-container styles from creating gaps */
  :global(.creative-container) {
    position: relative !important;
    top: auto !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
  }

  /* Match original creative section padding and alignment */
  /* Original had creative-container with margin: 2em and landing-row with margin: 1.5em */
  /* Text is naturally left-aligned (not in horizontal-align context in original) */
  .landing-row {
    text-align: left;
    margin: 1.5em;
  }

  /* Add padding to landing-main to match original creative-container margin */
  :global(.landing-main) {
    margin: 2em;
  }

  /* Mobile responsiveness */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .landing-row {
      margin: 1rem 0.5rem;
    }

    :global(.landing-main) {
      margin: 1em;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 576px) {
    :global(.nav-container) {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    :global(.nav-item) {
      padding: 0 0.5em;
    }

    .landing-row {
      margin: 1rem 0.5rem;
    }

    :global(.landing-main) {
      margin: 1em;
    }
  }
</style>
